data.name: Valtris Specialty Chemicals Company
data.description:
Valtris Specialty Chemicals is a leading global polymer additive company with a diverse product offering. Our product portfolio contains polymer additives, heat stabilizers, biocides, lubricants and advanced organics intermediates. Valtris provides specialty chemicals which serve a diverse set of end markets including building and construction, packaging, consumer goods, transportation, agriculture, flavor and fragrance, and oilfield additives.

Headquartered in Independence, Ohio, USA and with nine production facilities operating globally, Valtris offers and unmatched range of complimentary products for the specific needs of our diverse customer base.

Valtris team of world class, customer focused employees are committed to bringing value to our customers via quality materials, customer service excellence, superior technology, and innovative solutions.

data.name: Santicizer
data.description: Santicizer® Plasticizers offer all the benefits of high solvating plasticizers including compatibility in multiple polymer systems such as Polysulfide, PVC and Polyurethane.  Because of their high efficiency, less energy is required to fuse PVC formulations.  These materials are well suited for plastisol applications, but can easily be used in almost any polymer system that requires additional flexibility and softness.

data.name: Santicizer® 141

summary.name: Synonyms
items: 2-Ethylhexyl diphenyl phosphate, Diphenyl 2-ethylhexyl phosphate, Disflamoll DPO, EHDPP, Octicizer

data.description: Santicizer® 141 is a fast-fusing, non-halogen, fire retardant plasticizer used in multiple polymer systems. This plasticizer is recommended for applications where there is a need to reduce the risk of fire. This versatile additive has FDA clearances making it an option for applications that involve indirect food contact. In PVC, Santicizer® 141 acts as a high solvating plasticizer, offering performance, faster fusion and high plasticizing efficiency. Santicizer® 141 is also used as a lubricant additive, hydraulic fluid, and rubber processing aid.

data.name: Santicizer® Platinum G-2000
data.description:
Santicizer® Platinum G-2000 is an efficient bio-based
primary plasticizer that offers excellent heat stability,
enhanced processability, and lower volatility than
traditional General-Purpose Plasticizers. It can be
used in techniques such as extrusion, calendaring,
injection molding, rotational molding, and spread
coating. It can be used in rubbers, epoxy resins,
paints and coatings, as well as many other polymers.
Santicizer® Platinum G-2000 has earned the U.S.
Department of Agriculture (USDA) Certified Biobased
Product label.

data.name: Santicizer® 278
data.description: Santicizer® 278 is a fast fusing, benzyl phthalate plasticizer designed for use in multiple polymer systems and applications. This plasticizer is a high molecular weight alkyl benzyl phthalate that has compatibility in many polymer types, particularly in PVC. Santicizer® 278 is extremely permanent. It resists exudation and extraction and has very low volatility. Additionally, Santicizer® 278 has shown sound dampening benefits, and has benefits in wet applications of paint.

data.name: Santicizer® 148

summary.name: Synonyms
items: Diphenyl isodecyl phosphate, Isodecyl diphenyl phosphate

data.description: Santicizer® 148 is a fast-fusing, non-halogen, fire retardant plasticizer used in multiple polymer systems. This plasticizer is recommended for applications where there is a need to reduce the risk of fire. Santicizer® 148 helps to suppress smoke during combustion of materials it is used in. In PVC, Santicizer® 148 acts as a high solvating plasticizer, offering permanence, faster fusion and high plasticizing efficiency.

data.name: Santicizer® 1439
data.description: Santicizer® 1439 is a modified alkyl aryl phosphate ester for flexible PVC products that must meet stringent flame retardancy standards. Santicizer® 1439 is specially recommended for plastisol applications where lower viscosity is combined with high fire-retardancy of the end product.

data.name: Santicizer® Platinum P-330
data.description: Santicizer® Platinum P-330 is a non-phthalate, primary plasticizer with high performing product characteristics meant to outperform existing general purpose plasticizing alternatives. This plasticizer has some high solvating character to boost compatibility and plasticizing efficiency in multiple polymer systems. This product is highly recommended for PVC application where fast fusing would be a benefit.

data.name: Profilm™ 400
data.description: Profilm™ 400 is a zero VOC coalescing aid that is suitable for many architectural and industrial coating systems. Profilm™ 400 is water white in color, has no odor, and is safe to use. Profilm™ 400 is a versatile product that formulators can use to meet the stringent needs of their coating systems.

data.name: Santicizer® 154
data.description: Santicizer® 154 is a liquid, non-halogen, triaryl phosphate ester fire retardant plasticizer used in multiple polymer systems. This plasticizer is similar to tricresyl phosphate in performance properties, but without the neuro-toxicity associated with ortho-cresol materials. Within the Santicizer® family of plasticizers, Santicizer® 154 offers the best fire retardant properties. Santicizer® 154 is a great option in many applications where fire resistance is paramount, but plasticization is not a key property or where plasticization may need to be compensated for.

data.name: Santicizer® 160
data.description: Santicizer® 160 is a fast fusing, benzyl phthalate plasticizer designed for use in multiple polymer systems and applications. This plasticizer has compatibility in many polymer types, particularly in PVC. Santicizer® 160 can be used as a primary plasticizer or is often blended with general purpose plasticizers to offer faster fusion and better plasticizing efficiency. Together, these properties generate savings in faster production throughput, lower oven temperatures, and lower total plasticizer loadings. Santicizer® 160 is a well-recognized plasticizer utilized in many industrial PVC applications, processes like cleaning/purging, and as a carrier for biocides, pigments, and other additives.

data.name: Santicizer® 375
data.description: Santicizer® 375 is a viscosity modifier for use in PVC plastisols or organosols. This product is fugitive during any open heating processing, so it will be predominately absent in the finished good. The material can help compensate for viscosity rise that is a common shelf life problem for plastisols using fast fusing plasticizers. Additionally, Santicizer® 375 can allow for case hardening in applications that require surface rigidity.

data.name: Santicizer® 1462
data.description:
Santicizer® 1462 is a modified alkyl aryl phosphate ester for flexible PVC products that must meet stringent flame retardancy standards. Santicizer®
1462 is specially recommended for plastisol
applications where critical processing conditions must
be combined with high fire-retardancy of the end
product. In vinyl nitrile foams, Santicizer® 1462
imparts a significant level of fire retardancy and helps
foamed products meet certain specified flammability
performance criteria. Santicizer® 1462 also acts as a
processing aid and contributes to excellent cell
structure in chemically blown foams.

data.name: Santicizer® 2148
data.description:
Santicizer® 2148 is a non-halogen, low-smoke, alkyl
aryl fire retardant plasticizer used in multiple polymer
systems. This plasticizer is recommended for
applications where there is a need to reduce the risk
of fire and smoke. This versatile additive is
specifically designed to offer improved smoke
suppression.

data.name: Santicizer® 2248
data.description:

smoke, alkyl aryl fire retardant plasticizer used in

multiple polymer systems. This plasticizer is
recommended for applications where there is a need
to reduce the risk of fire, and especially smoke. This
versatile additive is specifically designed to offer

improved smoke suppression.
